doc.after: Astronomy is a natural science which is the study of celestial objects such as stars galaxies planets moons asteroids comets and nebulae the physics chemistry and evolution of such objects and phenomena that originate outside the atmosphere of Earth including supernovae explosions gamma ray bursts and cosmic microwave background radiation A related but distinct subject physical cosmology is concerned with studying the universe as a whole 1
